The Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) on Thursday sacked the entire technical crew of the team with immediate effect. Recall that Super Eagles were unable to qualify for the Qatar 2022 World Cup after losing to Ghana in a 1-1 draw on away-goal rule. According to a statement issued by the NFF Secretary General ,Dr Mohammed Sanusi, a new crew will be announced soon after a proper review. The statement reads, “The NFF has in the meantime withdrawn the two-and-half years contract offered the coaches and terminated the appointment of the entire technical crew of the team with immediate effect. “A new crew will be announced after a proper review to lead the new charge of reinvigorating the Super Eagles to face future challenges appropriately. “We thank the coaches and team officials for their service to the nation and wish them success in their future endeavours.”